cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces a definition for nonanticipative Rate Distortion Function (RDF) and derives the closed form expression of the optimal nonstationary reproduction distribution. These are core concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the properties of the RDF functional, such as compactness of the fidelity set and lower semicontinuity, which are relevant to machine learning. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses weak convergence of probability measures to show various properties of the RDF functional, which is a technique used in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the coding theorem derived in \cite{tatikonda2000}, which is relevant to social and information networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the optimal reproduction distribution, which is relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video compression.
